<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName LSID="Mycobank: MB 800589" authority="(Vain.) Schmitt &amp; Lumbsch" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ochrolechiaceae" genus="Varicellaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Varicellaria philippina" order="Pertusariales" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="philippina">Varicellaria philippina (Vain.) Schmitt &amp; Lumbsch</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="4" pageNumber="27">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="basionym">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Basionym.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pertusaria philippina" order="Pertusariales" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="philippina">Pertusaria philippina</taxonomicName>
Vain. Philipp. J. Sci., C, Bot. 8: 131. 1913. Type. Philippines, Mindanao, Lanao, Castra Keithley at Lake Lanao, 1907, Clemens 1302 (holotype TUR-V 6391!).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
This species is only known from the Philippines (
<bibRefCitation author="Wainio, EA" journalOrPublisher="Philippine Journal of Science, Section C Botany" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" pagination="99 - 137" title="Lichenes insularum philippinarum." volume="8" year="1913">Wainio 1913</bibRefCitation>
) and Papua New Guinea (
<bibRefCitation author="Elix, JA" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="7" pageNumber="30" pagination="17 - 35" title="The lichen genus Pertusaria (lichenised Ascomycotina) in Papua New Guinea and Australia: twelve new species and thirteen new reports." volume="64" year="1997">Elix et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
). We could not generate molecular data since no fresh material was available. Morphologically and chemically the species agrees with 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pertusaria velata" order="Pertusariales" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="velata">Pertusaria velata</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 2), but differs in having 2-spored asci.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
